  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "intro",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Regular -AR verbs",
      "body": "# Regular -AR verbs\n\nMost Spanish verbs are regular and end in **-ar**. You conjugate them with one fixed pattern: drop the **-ar** ending and add the personal ending.\n\nThe endings are always the same:\n\n| Person | Ending |\n|---|---|\n| yo | **-o** |\n| tú | **-as** |\n| él/ella | **-a** |\n| nosotros | **-amos** |\n| vosotros | **-áis** |\n| ellos/ellas | **-an** |\n\nExample *hablar* (to speak):\n\n| Person | Form |\n|---|---|\n| yo | **hablo** |\n| tú | **hablas** |\n| él/ella | **habla** |\n| nosotros | **hablamos** |\n| vosotros | **habláis** |\n| ellos/ellas | **hablan** |\n\nOnce you know this pattern, you can conjugate thousands of verbs — *estudiar*, *trabajar*, *comprar*, *cocinar*, and many more."
    },
    {
      "id": "step-vosotros",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "The vosotros form",
      "body": "## The vosotros form: habláis\n\nThe ending **-áis** (with an accent) is the informal plural \"you\". It is used **mainly in Spain**.\n\n- *Vosotros habláis español.* — You (all) speak Spanish.\n\nLatin America does not use this form. There you use **ustedes** together with the *ellos* form:\n\n- *Ustedes hablan español.* — You (all) speak Spanish.\n\nNote the **accent** on -áis: it marks the stressed syllable and is mandatory in writing."
    },
    {
      "id": "step-pronoun",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Dropping the subject pronoun",
      "body": "## The subject pronoun is usually dropped\n\nSpanish normally **drops** *yo*, *tú*, etc., because the ending already shows which person is meant.\n\n- *Hablo español.* — I speak Spanish. (not *Yo hablo español.*)\n- *¿Estudias mucho?* — Do you study a lot?\n\nThe ending **-o** can only mean *I*, the ending **-as** can only mean *you* — the pronoun would be redundant.\n\nYou **can** still use the pronoun for emphasis:\n\n- *Yo hablo español, pero él habla francés.* — *I* speak Spanish, but *he* speaks French."
    },
